{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":795,"text":"So when the White House was built"},{"time":2615,"text":"in the early 19th century, it was an open house."},{"time":5608,"text":"Neighbors came and went. Under President Adams,"},{"time":8744,"text":"a local dentist happened by."},{"time":10113,"text":"He wanted to shake the President's hand."},{"time":12704,"text":"The President dismissed the Secretary of State,"},{"time":14854,"text":"whom he was conferring with, and asked the dentist"},{"time":16772,"text":"if he would remove a tooth."},{"time":18582,"text":"Later, in the 1850s, under President Pierce,"},{"time":21640,"text":"he was known to have remarked"},{"time":23228,"text":"— probably the only thing he's known for —"},{"time":25797,"text":"when a neighbor passed by and said, \"I'd love to see"},{"time":28548,"text":"the beautiful house,\" and Pierce said to him,"},{"time":30813,"text":"\"Why my dear sir, of course you may come in."},{"time":33428,"text":"This isn't my house. It is the people's house.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":37153,"text":"Well, when I got to the White House in the beginning"},{"time":39225,"text":"of 2009, at the start of the Obama Administration,"},{"time":42445,"text":"the White House was anything but open."},{"time":45317,"text":"Bomb blast curtains covered my windows."},{"time":47845,"text":"We were running Windows 2000."},{"time":50024,"text":"Social media were blocked at the firewall."},{"time":52207,"text":"We didn't have a blog, let alone a dozen twitter accounts"},{"time":54747,"text":"like we have today."},{"time":56770,"text":"I came in to become the head of Open Government,"},{"time":59383,"text":"to take the values and the practices of transparency,"},{"time":62181,"text":"participation and collaboration, and instill them"},{"time":65594,"text":"into the way that we work, to open up government,"},{"time":68420,"text":"to work with people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69940,"text":"Now one of the things that we know"},{"time":72634,"text":"is that companies are very good at getting people to work"},{"time":75650,"text":"together in teams and in networks to make"},{"time":77898,"text":"very complex products, like cars and computers,"},{"time":81540,"text":"and the more complex the products are a society creates,"},{"time":85228,"text":"the more successful the society is over time."},{"time":88083,"text":"Companies make goods, but governments,"},{"time":90828,"text":"they make public goods. They work on the cure for cancer"},{"time":93948,"text":"and educating our children and making roads,"},{"time":96756,"text":"but we don't have institutions that are particularly good"},{"time":100397,"text":"at this kind of complexity. We don't have institutions"},{"time":102933,"text":"that are good at bringing our talents to bear,"},{"time":106050,"text":"at working with us in this kind of open and collaborative way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110512,"text":"So when we wanted to create our Open Government policy,"},{"time":112773,"text":"what did we do? We wanted, naturally, to ask public sector"},{"time":115349,"text":"employees how we should open up government."},{"time":118293,"text":"Turns out that had never been done before."},{"time":121525,"text":"We wanted to ask members of the public to help us"},{"time":124144,"text":"come up with a policy, not after the fact, commenting"},{"time":127422,"text":"on a rule after it's written, the way is typically the case,"},{"time":130805,"text":"but in advance. There was no legal precedent,"},{"time":134125,"text":"no cultural precedent, no technical way of doing this."},{"time":137267,"text":"In fact, many people told us it was illegal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140108,"text":"Here's the crux of the obstacle."},{"time":143221,"text":"Governments exist to channel the flow of two things,"},{"time":145822,"text":"really, values and expertise to and from government"},{"time":149316,"text":"and to and from citizens to the end of making decisions."},{"time":153165,"text":"But the way that our institutions are designed,"},{"time":155558,"text":"in our rather 18th-century, centralized model,"},{"time":158609,"text":"is to channel the flow of values through voting,"},{"time":162293,"text":"once every four years, once every two years, at best,"},{"time":164493,"text":"once a year. This is a rather anemic and thin way, in this"},{"time":168054,"text":"era of social media, for us to actually express our values."},{"time":172059,"text":"Today we have technology that lets us express ourselves"},{"time":174671,"text":"a great deal, perhaps a little too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177675,"text":"Then in the 19th century, we layer on"},{"time":179949,"text":"the concept of bureaucracy and the administrative state"},{"time":182356,"text":"to help us govern complex and large societies."},{"time":185499,"text":"But we've centralized these bureaucracies."},{"time":188731,"text":"We've entrenched them. And we know that"},{"time":191176,"text":"the smartest person always works for someone else."},{"time":193888,"text":"We need to only look around this room to know that"},{"time":196568,"text":"expertise and intelligence is widely distributed in society,"},{"time":200165,"text":"and not limited simply to our institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204336,"text":"Scientists have been studying in recent years"},{"time":206602,"text":"the phenomenon that they often describe as flow,"},{"time":209136,"text":"that the design of our systems, whether natural or social,"},{"time":212400,"text":"channel the flow of whatever runs through them."},{"time":215083,"text":"So a river is designed to channel the flow of water,"},{"time":218360,"text":"and the lightning bolt that comes out of a cloud channels"},{"time":220830,"text":"the flow of electricity, and a leaf is designed to channel"},{"time":224334,"text":"the flow of nutrients to the tree,"},{"time":226354,"text":"sometimes even having to route around an obstacle,"},{"time":229358,"text":"but to get that nutrition flowing."},{"time":232078,"text":"The same can be said for our social systems, for our"},{"time":234415,"text":"systems of government, where, at the very least,"},{"time":236903,"text":"flow offers us a helpful metaphor for understanding"},{"time":239918,"text":"what the problem is, what's really broken,"},{"time":242574,"text":"and the urgent need that we have, that we all feel today,"},{"time":246259,"text":"to redesign the flow of our institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249539,"text":"We live in a Cambrian era of big data, of social networks,"},{"time":254062,"text":"and we have this opportunity to redesign these institutions"},{"time":258331,"text":"that are actually quite recent."},{"time":261216,"text":"Think about it: What other business do you know,"},{"time":264456,"text":"what other sector of the economy, and especially one"},{"time":266856,"text":"as big as the public sector, that doesn't seek to reinvent"},{"time":270643,"text":"its business model on a regular basis?"},{"time":273547,"text":"Sure, we invest plenty in innovation. We invest"},{"time":276638,"text":"in broadband and science education and science grants,"},{"time":280602,"text":"but we invest far too little in reinventing and redesigning"},{"time":283953,"text":"the institutions that we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286553,"text":"Now, it's very easy to complain, of course, about"},{"time":288889,"text":"partisan politics and entrenched bureaucracy, and we love"},{"time":292353,"text":"to complain about government. It's a perennial pastime,"},{"time":295269,"text":"especially around election time, but"},{"time":297921,"text":"the world is complex. We soon will have 10 billion people,"},{"time":301307,"text":"many of whom will lack basic resources."},{"time":304180,"text":"So complain as we might, what actually can replace"},{"time":307498,"text":"what we have today?"},{"time":309809,"text":"What comes the day after the Arab Spring?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313916,"text":"Well, one attractive alternative that obviously presents itself"},{"time":317802,"text":"to us is that of networks. Right? Networks"},{"time":320562,"text":"like Facebook and Twitter. They're lean. They're mean."},{"time":323274,"text":"You've got 3,000 employees at Facebook"},{"time":325778,"text":"governing 900 million inhabitants."},{"time":328724,"text":"We might even call them citizens, because they've recently"},{"time":331467,"text":"risen up to fight against legislative incursion,"},{"time":334842,"text":"and the citizens of these networks work together"},{"time":337377,"text":"to serve each other in great ways."},{"time":340618,"text":"But private communities, private, corporate,"},{"time":343410,"text":"privatizing communities, are not bottom-up democracies."},{"time":346550,"text":"They cannot replace government."},{"time":348560,"text":"Friending someone on Facebook is not complex enough"},{"time":351662,"text":"to do the hard work of you and I collaborating"},{"time":354315,"text":"with each other and doing the hard work of governance."},{"time":358207,"text":"But social media do teach us something."},{"time":361145,"text":"Why is Twitter so successful? Because it opens up its platform."},{"time":365619,"text":"It opens up the API to allow hundreds of thousands"},{"time":368556,"text":"of new applications to be built on top of it, so that we can"},{"time":372027,"text":"read and process information in new and exciting ways."},{"time":376361,"text":"We need to think about how to open up the API"},{"time":378698,"text":"of government, and the way that we're going to do that,"},{"time":382759,"text":"the next great superpower is going to be the one"},{"time":386007,"text":"who can successfully combine the hierarchy of institution --"},{"time":391990,"text":"because we have to maintain those public values,"},{"time":394343,"text":"we have to coordinate the flow -- but with the diversity"},{"time":397262,"text":"and the pulsating life and the chaos and the excitement"},{"time":399927,"text":"of networks, all of us working together to build"},{"time":403023,"text":"these new innovations on top of our institutions,"},{"time":406724,"text":"to engage in the practice of governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408942,"text":"We have a precedent for this. Good old Henry II here,"},{"time":412075,"text":"in the 12th century, invented the jury."},{"time":415927,"text":"Powerful, practical, palpable model for handing power"},{"time":420152,"text":"from government to citizens."},{"time":422853,"text":"Today we have the opportunity, and we have"},{"time":426241,"text":"the imperative, to create thousands of new ways"},{"time":429742,"text":"of interconnecting between networks and institutions,"},{"time":432981,"text":"thousands of new kinds of juries: the citizen jury,"},{"time":435645,"text":"the Carrotmob, the hackathon, we are just beginning"},{"time":439322,"text":"to invent the models by which we can cocreate"},{"time":442376,"text":"the process of governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444124,"text":"Now, we don't fully have a picture of what this will look like"},{"time":446739,"text":"yet, but we're seeing pockets of evolution"},{"time":449361,"text":"emerging all around us -- maybe not even evolution,"},{"time":452343,"text":"I'd even start to call it a revolution -- in the way that we govern."},{"time":456152,"text":"Some of it's very high-tech,"},{"time":457636,"text":"and some of it is extremely low-tech,"},{"time":459690,"text":"such as the project that MKSS is running in Rajasthan,"},{"time":463060,"text":"India, where they take the spending data of the state"},{"time":466604,"text":"and paint it on 100,000 village walls,"},{"time":470047,"text":"and then invite the villagers to come and comment"},{"time":472342,"text":"who is on the government payroll, who's actually died,"},{"time":474830,"text":"what are the bridges that have been built to nowhere,"},{"time":477454,"text":"and to work together through civic engagement to save"},{"time":479798,"text":"real money and participate and have access to that budget."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483561,"text":"But it's not just about policing government."},{"time":485959,"text":"It's also about creating government."},{"time":487686,"text":"Spacehive in the U.K. is engaging in crowd-funding,"},{"time":490804,"text":"getting you and me to raise the money to build"},{"time":493489,"text":"the goalposts and the park benches that will actually"},{"time":496147,"text":"allow us to deliver better services in our communities."},{"time":499709,"text":"No one is better at this activity of actually getting us"},{"time":503347,"text":"to engage in delivering services,"},{"time":506587,"text":"sometimes where none exist, than Ushahidi."},{"time":509738,"text":"Created after the post-election riots in Kenya in 2008,"},{"time":514091,"text":"this crisis-mapping website and community is actually able"},{"time":518027,"text":"to crowdsource and target the delivery of"},{"time":520672,"text":"better rescue services to people trapped under the rubble,"},{"time":523763,"text":"whether it's after the earthquakes in Haiti,"},{"time":526219,"text":"or more recently in Italy."},{"time":528744,"text":"And the Red Cross too is training volunteers and Twitter"},{"time":531875,"text":"is certifying them, not simply to supplement existing"},{"time":534743,"text":"government institutions, but in many cases, to replace them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538779,"text":"Now what we're seeing lots of examples of, obviously,"},{"time":541787,"text":"is the opening up of government data,"},{"time":543474,"text":"not enough examples of this yet, but we're starting"},{"time":546474,"text":"to see this practice of people creating and generating"},{"time":550003,"text":"innovative applications on top of government data."},{"time":553472,"text":"There's so many examples I could have picked, and I"},{"time":555803,"text":"selected this one of Jon Bon Jovi. Some of you"},{"time":558969,"text":"may or may not know that he runs a soup kitchen"},{"time":561235,"text":"in New Jersey, where he caters to and serves the homeless"},{"time":563996,"text":"and particularly homeless veterans."},{"time":565689,"text":"In February, he approached the White House, and said,"},{"time":568467,"text":"\"I would like to fund a prize to create scalable national"},{"time":572312,"text":"applications, apps, that will help not only the homeless"},{"time":575839,"text":"but those who deliver services [to] them to do so better.\""},{"time":579274,"text":"February 2012 to June of 2012,"},{"time":582514,"text":"the finalists are announced in the competition."},{"time":585502,"text":"Can you imagine, in the bureaucratic world of yesteryear,"},{"time":588491,"text":"getting anything done in a four-month period of time?"},{"time":591237,"text":"You can barely fill out the forms in that amount of time,"},{"time":593373,"text":"let alone generate real, palpable innovations"},{"time":596237,"text":"that improve people's lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598128,"text":"And I want to be clear to mention that this open government"},{"time":601361,"text":"revolution is not about privatizing government,"},{"time":605138,"text":"because in many cases what it can do when we have"},{"time":608036,"text":"the will to do so is to deliver more progressive"},{"time":611132,"text":"and better policy than the regulations and the legislative"},{"time":615255,"text":"and litigation-oriented strategies"},{"time":618215,"text":"by which we make policy today."},{"time":620815,"text":"In the State of Texas, they regulate 515 professions,"},{"time":624542,"text":"from well-driller to florist."},{"time":626606,"text":"Now, you can carry a gun into a church in Dallas,"},{"time":629829,"text":"but do not make a flower arrangement without a license,"},{"time":632988,"text":"because that will land you in jail."},{"time":635604,"text":"So what is Texas doing? They're asking you and me,"},{"time":639621,"text":"using online policy wikis, to help not simply get rid of"},{"time":643709,"text":"burdensome regulations that impede entrepreneurship,"},{"time":647270,"text":"but to replace those regulations with more innovative"},{"time":650269,"text":"alternatives, sometimes using transparency in the creation"},{"time":653133,"text":"of new iPhone apps that will allows us"},{"time":655115,"text":"both to protect consumers and the public"},{"time":657388,"text":"and to encourage economic development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660899,"text":"That is a nice sideline of open government."},{"time":664053,"text":"It's not only the benefits that we've talked about with regard"},{"time":666764,"text":"to development. It's the economic benefits and the"},{"time":670221,"text":"job creation that's coming from this open innovation work."},{"time":674847,"text":"Sberbank, the largest and oldest bank in Russia,"},{"time":677667,"text":"largely owned by the Russian government,"},{"time":679467,"text":"has started practicing crowdsourcing, engaging"},{"time":682467,"text":"its employees and citizens in the public in developing innovations."},{"time":685819,"text":"Last year they saved a billion dollars, 30 billion rubles,"},{"time":690239,"text":"from open innovation, and they're pushing radically"},{"time":692996,"text":"the extension of crowdsourcing, not only from banking,"},{"time":695655,"text":"but into the public sector."},{"time":697698,"text":"And we see lots of examples of these innovators using"},{"time":700439,"text":"open government data, not simply to make apps,"},{"time":703289,"text":"but then to make companies and to hire people"},{"time":705351,"text":"to build them working with the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707652,"text":"So a lot of these innovations are local."},{"time":709782,"text":"In San Ramon, California, they published an iPhone app"},{"time":712888,"text":"in which they allow you or me to say we are certified"},{"time":716445,"text":"CPR-trained, and then when someone has a heart attack,"},{"time":720012,"text":"a notification goes out so that you"},{"time":722252,"text":"can rush over to the person over here and deliver CPR."},{"time":726208,"text":"The victim who receives bystander CPR"},{"time":728512,"text":"is more than twice as likely to survive."},{"time":730977,"text":"\"There is a hero in all of us,\" is their slogan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734652,"text":"But it's not limited to the local."},{"time":737195,"text":"British Columbia, Canada, is publishing a catalogue"},{"time":739856,"text":"of all the ways that its residents and citizens can engage"},{"time":742940,"text":"with the state in the cocreation of governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746658,"text":"Let me be very clear,"},{"time":749719,"text":"and perhaps controversial,"},{"time":751188,"text":"that open government is not"},{"time":753977,"text":"about transparent government."},{"time":755950,"text":"Simply throwing data over the transom doesn't change"},{"time":758868,"text":"how government works."},{"time":760280,"text":"It doesn't get anybody to do anything with that data"},{"time":762847,"text":"to change lives, to solve problems, and it doesn't change"},{"time":766556,"text":"government."},{"time":767828,"text":"What it does is it creates an adversarial relationship"},{"time":770847,"text":"between civil society and government"},{"time":772575,"text":"over the control and ownership of information."},{"time":775618,"text":"And transparency, by itself, is not reducing the flow"},{"time":778202,"text":"of money into politics, and arguably,"},{"time":780614,"text":"it's not even producing accountability as well as it might"},{"time":783347,"text":"if we took the next step of combining participation and"},{"time":786810,"text":"collaboration with transparency to transform how we work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790921,"text":"We're going to see this evolution really in two phases,"},{"time":793658,"text":"I think. The first phase of the open government revolution"},{"time":796947,"text":"is delivering better information from the crowd"},{"time":800723,"text":"into the center."},{"time":802117,"text":"Starting in 2005, and this is how this open government"},{"time":805064,"text":"work in the U.S. really got started,"},{"time":807018,"text":"I was teaching a patent law class to my students and"},{"time":809274,"text":"explaining to them how a single person in the bureaucracy"},{"time":813045,"text":"has the power to make a decision"},{"time":815176,"text":"about which patent application becomes the next patent,"},{"time":819661,"text":"and therefore monopolizes for 20 years the rights"},{"time":822403,"text":"over an entire field of inventive activity."},{"time":825410,"text":"Well, what did we do? We said, we can make a website,"},{"time":828322,"text":"we can make an expert network, a social network,"},{"time":830715,"text":"that would connect the network to the institution"},{"time":832987,"text":"to allow scientists and technologists to get"},{"time":835368,"text":"better information to the patent office"},{"time":838003,"text":"to aid in making those decisions."},{"time":840466,"text":"We piloted the work in the U.S. and the U.K. and Japan"},{"time":843098,"text":"and Australia, and now I'm pleased to report"},{"time":845891,"text":"that the United States Patent Office will be rolling out"},{"time":848147,"text":"universal, complete, and total openness,"},{"time":852612,"text":"so that all patent applications will now be open"},{"time":855658,"text":"for citizen participation, beginning this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859326,"text":"The second phase of this evolution — Yeah. (Applause)"},{"time":862262,"text":"They deserve a hand. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":865215,"text":"The first phase is in getting better information in."},{"time":867750,"text":"The second phase is in getting decision-making power out."},{"time":871607,"text":"Participatory budgeting has long been practiced"},{"time":874222,"text":"in Porto Alegre, Brazil."},{"time":875641,"text":"They're just starting it in the 49th Ward in Chicago."},{"time":878623,"text":"Russia is using wikis to get citizens writing law together,"},{"time":882159,"text":"as is Lithuania. When we start to see"},{"time":884511,"text":"power over the core functions of government"},{"time":886815,"text":"— spending, legislation, decision-making —"},{"time":890435,"text":"then we're well on our way to an open government revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894496,"text":"There are many things that we can do to get us there."},{"time":898327,"text":"Obviously opening up the data is one,"},{"time":900990,"text":"but the important thing is to create lots more --"},{"time":903353,"text":"create and curate -- lots more participatory opportunities."},{"time":907583,"text":"Hackathons and mashathons and working with data"},{"time":910281,"text":"to build apps is an intelligible way for people to engage"},{"time":913990,"text":"and participate, like the jury is,"},{"time":916490,"text":"but we're going to need lots more things like it."},{"time":919514,"text":"And that's why we need to start with our youngest people."},{"time":924165,"text":"We've heard talk here at TED about people"},{"time":926781,"text":"biohacking and hacking their plants with Arduino,"},{"time":930850,"text":"and Mozilla is doing work around the world in getting"},{"time":933894,"text":"young people to build websites and make videos."},{"time":937253,"text":"When we start by teaching young people that we live,"},{"time":939989,"text":"not in a passive society, a read-only society,"},{"time":943507,"text":"but in a writable society, where we have the power"},{"time":946074,"text":"to change our communities, to change our institutions,"},{"time":949698,"text":"that's when we begin to really put ourselves on the pathway"},{"time":952834,"text":"towards this open government innovation,"},{"time":956045,"text":"towards this open government movement,"},{"time":957754,"text":"towards this open government revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960277,"text":"So let me close by saying that I think the important thing"},{"time":962523,"text":"for us to do is to talk about and demand this revolution."},{"time":968382,"text":"We don't have words, really, to describe it yet."},{"time":971677,"text":"Words like equality and fairness and the traditional"},{"time":973902,"text":"elections, democracy, these are not really great terms yet."},{"time":978269,"text":"They're not fun enough. They're not exciting enough"},{"time":981017,"text":"to get us engaged in this tremendous opportunity"},{"time":984336,"text":"that awaits us. But I would argue that if we want to see"},{"time":987744,"text":"the kinds of innovations, the hopeful and exciting"},{"time":990447,"text":"innovations that we hear talked about here at TED,"},{"time":993111,"text":"in clean energy, in clean education,"},{"time":995288,"text":"in development, if we want to see those adopted"},{"time":997879,"text":"and we want to see those scaled,"},{"time":1000135,"text":"we want to see them become the governance of tomorrow,"},{"time":1002927,"text":"then we must all participate,"},{"time":1004632,"text":"then we must get involved."},{"time":1006130,"text":"We must open up our institutions, and like the leaf,"},{"time":1009340,"text":"we must let the nutrients flow throughout our body politic,"},{"time":1013534,"text":"throughout our culture, to create open institutions"},{"time":1016734,"text":"to create a stronger democracy, a better tomorrow."},{"time":1019403,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}